    metric: metric,
    storage: storage
)

try await engine.ingest(
    id: "vec-1",
    vector: embedding,
    ctx: context
)

await engine.reconcile()

DUMEgov Layer:

let gov = DUMEGovEngine(
    engine: strictEngine,
    policy: policy,
    actorID: "system-node-1"
)

try await gov.ingest(
    id: "vec-1",
    vector: embedding,
    ctx: context
)
When to Use Each
Strict Engine
Deterministic behavior required
Multi-node reproducibility required
Debugging correctness critical
Hybrid Engine
Throughput is priority
System conditions are dynamic
Availability > strict consistency
DUMEgov
Auditability required
Compliance or verification required
System integrity must be provable
Design Philosophy

DUME separates system truth into three layers:

Computation truth → Engines
Storage truth → Envelopes
Verification truth → DUMEgov

No single layer is fully trusted alone.

